<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="multiple">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Taxon classification Animalia Hymenoptera Chrysididae</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum chalybaeum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybaeum">Hedychrum chalybaeum Dahlbom, 1854</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum chalybaeum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybaeum">Hedychrum chalybaeum</taxonomicName>
Dahlbom, 1854: 64.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Length 4-6 mm. The male is easy to differentiate from other 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hedychrum</taxonomicName>
species by its entirely green-blue body. Therefore it superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga metallica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">Holopyga metallica</taxonomicName>
and the male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga fervida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervida">Holopyga fervida</taxonomicName>
. The female is completely differently coloured: the vertex, pronotum, mesoscutum, mesoscutellum and dorsum of the metasoma are bright red, whereas the ventral and lateral parts of the head and mesosoma, including the legs, are blue or greenish. The pubescence is dark brown and the apicomedial tubercle on S3 of the female is very small.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Latvia, Lithuania. Very rare. The species has been recorded in one locality in Latvia (
<bibRefCitation author="Tumss, V" journalOrPublisher="Zoologijas muzeja raksti" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="11 - 26" title="Materiali Latvijas PSR dzēlējplēvsparnu (Hymenoptera, Aculeata) faunai." volume="14" year="1976">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tumšs">Tumss</normalizedToken>
1976
</bibRefCitation>
) and in three localities in Lithuania (
<bibRefCitation author="Wengris, J" journalOrPublisher="Sectio E (Zoologia)" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" pagination="1 - 19" title="Materialy do fauny blonkoskrzydlych (Hymenoptera) najblizszych okolic Wilna. Studia societatis scientiarum Torunensis." volume="6" year="1962">Wengris 1962</bibRefCitation>
). - Trans-Palearctic: from western Europe to Russian Far East, Mongolia and China (
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 128" title="An annotated checklist of the chrysidid wasps (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) from China." url="10.3897/zookeys.455.6557" volume="455" year="2014">Rosa et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="biology">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Habitat: sparsely vegetated sand and loess areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Kunz, PX" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte zu den Veroeffentlichungen fuer Naturschutz und Landschaftspflege in Baden-Wuerttemberg" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 188" title="Die Goldwespen (Chrysididae) Baden-Wuerttembergs. Taxonomie, Bestimmung, Verbreitung, Kartierung und Oekologie. - Mit einem Bestimmungsschluessel fuer die deutschen Arten." volume="77" year="1994">Kunz 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Adults visit flowers of 
<taxonomicName authority="Steud., 1840" authorityName="Steud." authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heteroptera" order="Apiales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heteroptera" order="Hemiptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Heinrich, J" journalOrPublisher="Nachrihten des Naturwissenschaftlichen Museums der Stad Aschaffenburg" pageId="94" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 28" title="Beitrag zur Hymenopteren-fauna des westlichen Unterfranken. 1. Teil, Chrysididae." volume="71" year="1964">Heinrich 1964</bibRefCitation>
). Flight period: July to August. Host: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Cerceris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerceris interrupta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interrupta">Cerceris interrupta</taxonomicName>
(Panzer) (
<taxonomicName family="Crabronidae" lsidName="" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="family">Crabronidae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Schmid-Egger, C" journalOrPublisher="Verlag Regionalkultur, Ubstadt-Weiher" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="257 - 306" title="Die Wildbienen- und Wespenfauna der oberrheinischen Trockenaue im suedwestlichen Baden-Wuerttemberg (Hymenoptera: Aculeata; Evanioidea)." volumeTitle="Vom Wildstrom zur Trockenaue. Natur und Geschichte der Flusslandschaft am suedlichen Oberrhein." year="2000">Schmid-Egger 2000</bibRefCitation>
). Host records implicating 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Bembecinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembecinus tridens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridens">Bembecinus tridens</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius) (
<taxonomicName family="Crabronidae" lsidName="" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="family">Crabronidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Bembicinae">Bembicinae</taxonomicName>
) are probably erroneous, as supporting evidence is lacking.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
